1
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:16,467
This is the least
I can do for you.

2
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:19,267
Let me do this for you.

3
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:21,200
Did I see it right?

4
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:24,133
She can't be Yenyen's mom...

5
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:27,800
I will never let anyone
tear us apart.

6
00:00:27,867 --> 00:00:31,000
Yenyen knows the truth,
and she didn't tell me!

7
00:00:31,067 --> 00:00:37,367
Amanda came here and declared
war on my territory!

8
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:38,733
You know what's worse?

9
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:40,900
Your son saw what you did.

10
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:43,833
Red just got back
from a tragedy.

11
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:45,967
Do you think this will help him?

12
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:49,267
Your mom went to jail because
she killed my brother.

13
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:51,733
My mom is innocent, Red.

14
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:53,733
I know that she's telling
the truth.

15
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:56,233
My mom is innocent.

16
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,533
What are you saying?

17
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,533
What are you trying to say?

18
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,400
Were you there? Did you see
what happened?

19
00:01:01,467 --> 00:01:04,467
- Did you see everything?
- Yes, Red! I was there!

20
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:07,733
I saw when your former driver
forced his way in your house.

21
00:01:07,833 --> 00:01:10,733
That's not what my mom told me.

22
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:13,567
I'm not asking you
to believe me.

23
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:15,833
But that's what I saw.

24
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:18,767
We can't meet halfway.

25
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:21,467
We're better off apart...

26
00:01:21,533 --> 00:01:25,000
for everyone's peace of mind.

27
00:02:29,067 --> 00:02:31,833
Eden, why are you crying?

28
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:37,967
Red found out the truth.

29
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:40,933
What?

30
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,733
Oh my God.

31
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,967
Hold on...

32
00:02:46,033 --> 00:02:50,733
What will happen now
that Red knows the truth?

33
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:55,200
I don't know, Auntie.

34
00:02:55,267 --> 00:02:58,467
All I know is that I have
to stay away from him.

35
00:02:58,533 --> 00:03:03,600
Oh, dear. Honestly, that's what
your mom is afraid of.

36
00:03:03,667 --> 00:03:07,500
She told me how worried
she was for you.

37
00:03:07,567 --> 00:03:14,233
She said she was worried you
might cross paths with Red,

38
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:17,600
Rina's son.

39
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:22,100
She has no idea that the two
of you've crossed paths already.

40
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:25,067
Yen, it could be a sign.

41
00:03:25,133 --> 00:03:29,067
Maybe you need to tell your mom
the truth.

42
00:03:30,167 --> 00:03:33,433
You're probably right, Auntie.

43
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:36,100
I'm going to tell my mom
everything.

44
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:38,167
I will tell her the truth.

45
00:03:40,567 --> 00:03:44,467
Hey, you're home.

46
00:03:44,533 --> 00:03:49,567
Come on, let's all go upstairs
so we can have dinner.

47
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:50,567
Mom...

48
00:03:50,633 --> 00:03:52,633
Yeah?

49
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,000
I have something important
to tell you.

50
00:03:56,800 --> 00:04:00,067
Are you okay? What is it?

51
00:04:10,067 --> 00:04:11,000
Bro, that's enough.

52
00:04:11,067 --> 00:04:13,000
You're drunk.

53
00:04:13,067 --> 00:04:14,900
I'm not drunk, bro. I'm fine.

54
00:04:23,533 --> 00:04:25,033
Red! Colby, what on earth!

55
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:26,533
Why did you let
him drink too much?

56
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,867
You know that he can't handle
alcohol.

57
00:04:28,967 --> 00:04:30,967
Sab, I've been trying to stop
him from drinking.

58
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:32,767
But he didn't listen.

59
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:34,567
I think he has a problem.

60
00:04:34,633 --> 00:04:36,033
That's why I called you.

61
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:40,633
Sab...

62
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:43,067
Did you come here to save me
from my misery?

63
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:45,900
What are you talking about?

64
00:04:47,967 --> 00:04:53,000
I'm in so much pain right now,
Sab.

65
00:04:57,533 --> 00:04:58,767
I haven't felt this for a while.

66
00:04:58,833 --> 00:05:02,533
The first time I felt like
this was when my brother died.

67
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:05,100
Is it about Yenyen?

68
00:05:06,167 --> 00:05:07,867
Did something happen?

69
00:05:10,033 --> 00:05:11,100
Red?

70
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,500
Oh my God! Oh my God!

71
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:19,467
Colby, help me. Hurry up!

72
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:20,967
- Let's go.
- Red, that's enough.

73
00:05:21,033 --> 00:05:22,900
We'll get you home.

74
00:05:22,967 --> 00:05:24,167
Come on, help me.

75
00:05:25,567 --> 00:05:31,300
I want to let you know that...

76
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:40,733
if you're worried that I'll
cross paths with Rina's son...

77
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:42,600
don't worry.

78
00:05:42,667 --> 00:05:44,700
That will never happen.

79
00:05:44,767 --> 00:05:47,833
First of all, we don't know
each other.

80
00:05:49,067 --> 00:05:52,933
And if ever he tries to approach
me, I'll stay away.

81
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,067
I won't let them hurt me.

82
00:05:56,133 --> 00:05:58,333
I'm glad to hear that.

83
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:03,167
We'll just stay away from them.

84
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:04,733
I'm sorry, Eden.

85
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:08,167
I didn't mean to trouble you
about what happened last time.

86
00:06:09,433 --> 00:06:12,967
I won't let them come near you
and hurt you.

87
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,867
Come on.

88
00:06:17,933 --> 00:06:19,667
Let's go upstairs so we can eat.

89
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:21,767
Okay, go on ahead.

90
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:23,000
We'll be right there.

91
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:25,200
Okay.

92
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:30,667
What was that, Yen?

93
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:32,033
Auntie! Uncle!

94
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,500
- Oh my God!
- Hey, Red.

95
00:06:33,567 --> 00:06:35,833
What happened?

96
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:38,600
- Okay, okay.
- Red?

97
00:06:38,667 --> 00:06:41,700
- Here, here, here.
- Slowly. Thank you.

98
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,267
What happened, Red?

99
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:45,000
I picked him up at the bar,
Auntie.

100
00:06:45,067 --> 00:06:47,267
He's been drinking.

101
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:49,267
I'm sure he's hanging
out with his friends.

102
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:51,667
Look at him. He drinks
more than he can handle.

103
00:06:51,733 --> 00:06:54,100
Victor, my son's not like this.

104
00:06:54,167 --> 00:06:56,267
I mean, yes, he drinks
occasionally.

105
00:06:56,333 --> 00:07:00,367
But it's the first time
seeing him like this.

106
00:07:00,433 --> 00:07:02,467
Unless he has...

107
00:07:02,533 --> 00:07:04,367
She's right, Uncle.

108
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:06,833
I think Red is going through
something right now.

109
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:09,167
He keeps on saying about
how painful he is feeling

110
00:07:09,233 --> 00:07:13,067
right now. It makes me wonder.

111
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:14,567
Red.

112
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:18,500
- Slowly.
- Mom...

113
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:21,333
About Amanda...

114
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,867
What about Amanda?

115
00:07:23,933 --> 00:07:25,767
I already know the truth.

116
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:28,467
What's the truth?

117
00:07:30,433 --> 00:07:33,667
She's connected...

118
00:07:33,733 --> 00:07:36,933
She's connected to...

119
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,533
I thought you would tell her
the truth

120
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,200
about you and Red?

121
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:45,767
Auntie, I don't want her
to worry.

122
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:48,567
She won't stop worrying
if she finds out

123
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:51,167
that Red was the guy I was
with on the island.

124
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:56,000
Even if I tell her that we'll
stay away from each other.

125
00:07:56,067 --> 00:08:01,000
She won't stop thinking about
my connection with Red.

126
00:08:01,067 --> 00:08:06,233
She'll be worrying about me
at all times.

127
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:09,333
I don't want that to happen.

128
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:14,333
I would rather forget whatever
I had with Red...

129
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,333
without letting my mom
know the truth.

130
00:08:24,033 --> 00:08:26,733
She's connected to whom?

131
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:31,200
She's connected to...

132
00:08:31,267 --> 00:08:32,767
Red...

133
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:35,400
- Red?
- Red?

134
00:08:35,467 --> 00:08:37,233
Red!

135
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:39,767
Oh my God, we should lay him
down for now.

136
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:45,333
She's connected to whom?

137
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:47,833
I don't know.

138
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:50,600
We should leave him alone
for now, Hon.

139
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:52,667
We need to bring him
to his room.

140
00:08:52,733 --> 00:08:53,933
So he can get some rest.

141
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,133
But he wants to tell us
something!

142
00:08:56,233 --> 00:08:59,500
Red wants to say something
about Amanda.

143
00:08:59,567 --> 00:09:01,300
Let it pass, Rina.

144
00:09:01,367 --> 00:09:02,867
He's drunk.

145
00:09:02,933 --> 00:09:04,400
He's not in his right mind.

146
00:09:04,467 --> 00:09:08,500
He's been thinking and talking
nonsense.

147
00:09:08,567 --> 00:09:10,333
What about Amanda, Red?

148
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,967
Take it slow.
Be careful, please.

149
00:09:24,067 --> 00:09:25,200
Let's let him rest.

150
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:29,100
Victor...

151
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,033
I'm worried about Red.

152
00:09:34,267 --> 00:09:38,467
Why is he being like
this all of a sudden?

153
00:09:38,533 --> 00:09:41,267
And he even said something
about Amanda...

154
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:43,333
being related to whoever.

155
00:09:45,667 --> 00:09:46,967
It only means one thing.

156
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:52,167
Our son is getting affected
by your quarrel with Amanda.

157
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:58,133
He saw how the two of you fight.

158
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:01,733
How do you expect him to react?

159
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:03,967
Red just got back to us.

160
00:10:04,033 --> 00:10:09,367
And we're given this chance
to make it up to him.

161
00:10:09,433 --> 00:10:12,200
I don't want to lose him again.

162
00:10:12,267 --> 00:10:14,367
Rina...

163
00:10:14,433 --> 00:10:18,233
Red is all we have left.

164
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:20,533
We only have Red.

165
00:10:39,133 --> 00:10:41,233
You're up. Good.

166
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:42,233
Good morning.

167
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,367
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

168
00:10:43,433 --> 00:10:45,467
Let's have breakfast. I made you
some toast and eggs.

169
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:46,667
Thank you.

170
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:50,400
Son...

171
00:10:50,467 --> 00:10:51,967
next time you get drunk,

172
00:10:52,033 --> 00:10:54,500
just make sure you can come home
on your own.

173
00:10:54,567 --> 00:10:57,133
Don't let a girl bring you home.

174
00:10:57,200 --> 00:11:00,033
That's embarrassing to Sab.

175
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:02,633
I'm sorry, Dad. It won't happen
again.

176
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:04,633
That's okay.

177
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:07,200
And next time you want something
out of your chest,

178
00:11:07,267 --> 00:11:08,800
your dad and I are here.

179
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,733
You can talk to us.

180
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,633
So, what happened?

181
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:16,400
Nothing.

182
00:11:16,467 --> 00:11:17,433
Nothing's wrong, Mom.

183
00:11:18,733 --> 00:11:22,100
How can you say nothing's wrong?

184
00:11:22,167 --> 00:11:26,167
You mentioned Amanda's name
last night.

185
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:31,200
Son, I'm sorry if you're getting
affected by my issue

186
00:11:31,267 --> 00:11:33,767
with Amanda.

187
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:37,933
I promise you that we will not
talk about her anymore.

188
00:11:42,133 --> 00:11:44,333
I saw everything.

189
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:49,000
I saw it when my mom tried
to save your brother.

190
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:50,967
That's why I know she's telling
the truth.

191
00:11:51,033 --> 00:11:53,000
My mom is innocent.

192
00:11:54,033 --> 00:11:57,700
She can't ruin us again,
especially now that you know...

193
00:11:57,767 --> 00:11:59,633
Mom, Dad...

194
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:10,767
Are you sure that Amanda
had something to do

195
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:14,300
with Angelo's death?

196
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:17,267
Is it true that her daughter
was with her

197
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:18,700
when the crime happened?

198
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:22,367
That her daughter witnessed
what happened?

199
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:26,067
Don't you think you
were mistaken?

200
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:28,633
What if Amanda's innocent,

201
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:31,133
and you put her in jail
for something she didn't do?

202
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:40,467
Red, where are all these
questions coming from?

203
00:12:40,533 --> 00:12:43,033
Why are you asking this?

204
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:44,500
What are you trying to say?

205
00:12:44,567 --> 00:12:46,867
That we're making things up?

206
00:12:46,933 --> 00:12:49,733
I just want to know
what really happened.

207
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:51,533
I deserve to know the truth,
right?

208
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:57,067
So you believe that woman
over us?

209
00:12:57,133 --> 00:12:59,333
I knew it!

210
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,600
Amanda talked to you.

211
00:13:00,667 --> 00:13:03,100
She put all those ideas
in your head!

212
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:04,900
Right? Am I right?

213
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:08,067
So it's true. It's true
that her daughter was there.

214
00:13:08,133 --> 00:13:10,267
And she witnessed the crime.

215
00:13:10,333 --> 00:13:12,700
And it's also true that Amanda
could be innocent.

216
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:18,067
Look, that woman was sentenced
to jail because she was guilty!

217
00:13:18,133 --> 00:13:19,433
But she got out!

218
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,300
Okay, enough! Enough!

219
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:25,667
Can you see yourself right now?

220
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:29,300
You're fighting because
of that woman!

221
00:13:29,367 --> 00:13:31,933
And as for you, young man,

222
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:34,500
our stand will not change!

223
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:38,367
That woman is responsible
for the death of your brother!

224
00:13:38,433 --> 00:13:40,300
Even if she got out of jail,

225
00:13:40,367 --> 00:13:42,500
it won't change anything!

226
00:14:11,367 --> 00:14:13,367
I miss Coach, Friend.

227
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:18,567
Too bad she won't see
our final season.

228
00:14:18,633 --> 00:14:20,133
Here I go again.

229
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:22,567
Me and my big mouth.

230
00:14:22,633 --> 00:14:25,900
I should stop talking now,
right?

231
00:14:25,967 --> 00:14:26,900
Oh, wow!

232
00:14:26,967 --> 00:14:31,033
She's not listening!

233
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:32,800
Eden, I heard Red didn't
go to school today!

234
00:14:32,867 --> 00:14:34,833
- What?
- See?

235
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:36,400
Whenever you hear
the word Red...

236
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:38,867
Red is the password to get
your attention.

237
00:14:38,933 --> 00:14:40,900
You're so great.

238
00:14:40,967 --> 00:14:44,167
I'm sorry, Friend.
I have a lot on my mind.

239
00:14:44,233 --> 00:14:47,900
I feel guilty because I didn't
tell my mom the truth about Red.

240
00:14:47,967 --> 00:14:51,733
And I still feel guilty here
at school.

241
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:52,800
Eden...

242
00:14:52,867 --> 00:14:56,267
Red feels the same way you do.

243
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:58,367
If you're miserable right now,
so is he.

244
00:14:58,433 --> 00:15:00,433
That's why he didn't go
to school today.

245
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:03,467
I wish I didn't meet him.

246
00:15:03,567 --> 00:15:09,267
I wish I'd never gotten
attached to him.

247
00:15:09,333 --> 00:15:11,567
It's so hard.

248
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:15,100
It's hard to unload things
that made you happy once.

249
00:15:15,167 --> 00:15:17,700
Eden, you have your mom.

250
00:15:17,767 --> 00:15:21,833
Make her the reason
to be happy again.

251
00:15:21,900 --> 00:15:24,000
I don't want to think about it,

252
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:29,800
but her past is why I feel
confused and sad.

253
00:16:06,167 --> 00:16:11,233
A heinous crime happened
in a village in Quezon City.

254
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:13,733
A young man died after getting
hit by a car driven

255
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:16,133
by the suspect, Raul Cortez.

256
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:20,800
The CCTV footage at the victim's
house showed

257
00:16:20,867 --> 00:16:23,167
the Ramos family's maid
and the suspect's accomplice,

258
00:16:23,233 --> 00:16:28,067
Amanda Sta. Maria, let him in.

259
00:16:28,133 --> 00:16:31,567
The police arrested the
suspect's accomplice

260
00:16:31,633 --> 00:16:38,633
while Raul Cortez died from
his encounter with the police.

261
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:41,833
According to SPO1
Norman Hernandez,

262
00:16:41,933 --> 00:16:44,400
the investigator handling
the case,

263
00:16:44,467 --> 00:16:47,433
there is no other witness
besides the CCTV

264
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:50,333
and Amanda Sta. Maria's
daughter.

265
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:53,000
So Yenyen's telling the truth.

266
00:16:53,067 --> 00:16:55,400
She was here when the crime took
place.

267
00:16:55,467 --> 00:16:58,167
Red?

268
00:16:58,233 --> 00:17:00,700
What about Yenyen?

269
00:17:00,767 --> 00:17:02,267
What are you watching?

270
00:17:08,267 --> 00:17:10,900
Nothing, Dad. It's just for...

271
00:17:10,967 --> 00:17:12,133
research.

272
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:15,800
I need to research the wild
animal we talked about

273
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:17,833
on the island.

274
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:18,967
It's nothing.

275
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:28,700
About earlier...

276
00:17:28,767 --> 00:17:31,233
I just want to apologize.

277
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:35,200
I don't want us to quarrel just
because of Amanda.

278
00:17:35,267 --> 00:17:37,667
Red, we are your family.

279
00:17:37,733 --> 00:17:41,233
So, I expect you to believe us.

280
00:17:43,767 --> 00:17:46,833
I'm sorry about what I said.

281
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:51,500
It wasn't my intention
to hurt you or Mom.

282
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:53,600
I understand.

283
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:56,133
So, please.

284
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,833
I'm begging you.

285
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:05,200
Just stay away from Amanda

286
00:18:05,267 --> 00:18:08,433
to keep her from bringing
more trouble to our family.

287
00:18:22,633 --> 00:18:25,000
I need to gather
more information.

288
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:40,700
Your brother's case has been
closed for a long time now.

289
00:18:40,767 --> 00:18:45,333
The suspect was dead,
and his accomplice went to jail.

290
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:49,733
Mrs. Amanda Sta. Maria
has been released.

291
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:52,733
What else do you need to know?

292
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:55,300
I just want to know

293
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:59,800
if it's possible that Amanda had
nothing to do with the crime.

294
00:18:59,867 --> 00:19:02,467
That she's innocent.

295
00:19:02,533 --> 00:19:05,933
I don't want to think
she just got unlucky

296
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,633
for being there when
the crime happened.

297
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:12,900
And what's even more unfortunate
is that she was seen on the CCTV

298
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:15,833
letting the suspect
inside the house.

299
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:18,100
That was the strong evidence
against her.

300
00:19:18,167 --> 00:19:20,233
Is it possible that she could
have been set up?

301
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:22,600
And also, her daughter
was there.

302
00:19:22,667 --> 00:19:23,700
Someone witnessed the crime.

303
00:19:23,767 --> 00:19:25,767
Didn't they use her testimony?

304
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:27,967
It was useless.

305
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:31,400
It couldn't be used in court.

306
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:35,533
The CCTV footage where she was
seen letting the suspect

307
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:38,900
inside the house
is strong evidence

308
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:42,900
that Amanda is an accessory
to the crime.

309
00:19:42,967 --> 00:19:45,600
But I admit,

310
00:19:45,667 --> 00:19:53,167
my investigation suggested
that Amanda could be innocent.

311
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:56,667
Every time she would
give her testimony,

312
00:19:56,733 --> 00:20:05,133
I saw how she would calmly
try to prove her innocence.

313
00:20:05,233 --> 00:20:07,467
She did everything...

314
00:20:07,533 --> 00:20:11,567
she didn't give up for the sake
her daughter.

315
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:17,067
I thought she would be
acquitted.

316
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:18,167
What happened?

317
00:20:18,233 --> 00:20:20,400
How come she went to jail?

318
00:20:20,467 --> 00:20:24,733
The case took a fast turn.

319
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:28,233
I don't know what
Attorney Gualvez did

320
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:33,767
to close the case and get Mrs.
Amanda Sta. Maria sentenced.

321
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,567
No! No!

322
00:20:45,633 --> 00:20:47,933
That is not enough, Attorney!

323
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,467
How can I get peace of mind?

324
00:20:49,533 --> 00:20:51,867
I can't bring my child
back to life!

325
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:53,367
Meanwhile, Amanda is what?

326
00:20:53,433 --> 00:20:54,833
She got out.

327
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,600
She's with her daughter now.

328
00:20:56,667 --> 00:20:58,767
And you know what is worse?

329
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:02,267
She gets to talk to my son Red!

330
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:05,633
And she's been trying to poison
his head!

331
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,700
Yes! If you can do that,
then get it done!

332
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,667
I don't care how much I have to
pay you!

333
00:21:13,733 --> 00:21:15,933
We did it before, right?

334
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,333
The case was expedited.

335
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:20,200
Then do it again!

336
00:21:20,267 --> 00:21:23,800
I just want that woman
to rot in jail!

337
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:27,000
So, it's true?

338
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:34,867
You paid them off to put that
Amanda in jail?

339
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:45,233
It's not what you think,
Red, okay?

340
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:46,600
Let me explain.

341
00:21:46,667 --> 00:21:49,633
No. But I heard it clearly.

342
00:21:49,700 --> 00:21:52,133
You said you used your money
and connections

343
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:55,000
to expedite the case.

344
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:58,100
Mom, what if she really
is innocent?

345
00:21:58,167 --> 00:22:00,400
That woman is guilty!

346
00:22:00,467 --> 00:22:03,133
That wench is as guilty as hell!
Okay?

347
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:08,567
I'm sure she had something to do
with your brother's death!

348
00:22:08,633 --> 00:22:11,500
Okay, so maybe I would
abuse my resources

349
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:14,667
to make things move faster,
but still, she's guilty!

350
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:16,400
What if she's innocent?

351
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:19,300
Then we didn't give my brother
justice!

352
00:22:19,367 --> 00:22:21,800
Look, I did all that
to give justice precisely

353
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:24,767
to your brother. I am sure!

354
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:28,067
She's guilty, Red! I'm sure!

355
00:22:28,133 --> 00:22:30,833
Now why are you so affected
about this?

356
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:33,033
Because I'm affected by it!

357
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:35,867
My life's at stake here!

358
00:22:35,933 --> 00:22:39,600
How are you affected by this,
Red?

359
00:22:39,667 --> 00:22:41,400
Red, come back!

360
00:22:41,467 --> 00:22:43,400
Red!

361
00:22:43,467 --> 00:22:44,800
Where are you going?

362
00:22:52,367 --> 00:22:55,500
Yenyen, what's going on between
you and Red?

363
00:22:55,567 --> 00:22:58,200
Whatever Red and I
are going through,

364
00:22:58,267 --> 00:23:01,500
you have nothing to do with it.

365
00:23:01,567 --> 00:23:04,667
I have something to do with it
because I'm affected by it.

366
00:23:04,733 --> 00:23:06,100
He was so drunk the other night.

367
00:23:06,167 --> 00:23:08,400
And now he didn't show up
in class.

368
00:23:08,467 --> 00:23:11,333
As far as I know,
he's not like that.

369
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:13,433
Ever since he met you,

370
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,800
you ruined not just
our relationship.

371
00:23:15,867 --> 00:23:18,000
You're also ruining his life!

372
00:23:18,067 --> 00:23:20,233
Sabina, you don't
know what's going on.

373
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:25,967
So, if you don't know anything,
stay out of it.

374
00:23:26,067 --> 00:23:27,500
How dare you!

375
00:23:27,567 --> 00:23:28,633
This is Red we're talking about.

376
00:23:28,700 --> 00:23:30,900
So, I'm automatically involved.

377
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:33,300
And I'm warning you, Yenyen.

378
00:23:33,367 --> 00:23:35,133
Whatever trouble you're in...

379
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:36,133
what you're fighting about...

380
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,700
or whatever you're deal is...

381
00:23:37,767 --> 00:23:40,233
can you just leave
Red out of it?

382
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:41,800
And you!

383
00:23:41,867 --> 00:23:43,500
At this point,

384
00:23:43,567 --> 00:23:46,067
I don't know if your brain
is slow

385
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:47,600
or if something's wrong
with your ear!

386
00:23:47,667 --> 00:23:50,733
But I'm telling you this
for the hundredth time,

387
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:53,067
stay away from us!

388
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:55,367
You still haven't changed,
have you?

389
00:23:55,467 --> 00:23:57,133
The same that I haven't
forgotten

390
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:59,400
what you did to me
on the island.

391
00:23:59,467 --> 00:24:00,867
Don't worry.

392
00:24:00,933 --> 00:24:05,133
If you're doing this to get Red
back, he's all yours.

393
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:06,267
If you like, I can give you
a lace,

394
00:24:06,333 --> 00:24:10,333
so you can keep him with you.

395
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:12,400
Red and I broke up, Sabina.

396
00:24:12,467 --> 00:24:15,800
And we are never getting back
together.

397
00:24:15,867 --> 00:24:17,567
Happy?

398
00:24:17,633 --> 00:24:19,500
Very.

399
00:24:26,567 --> 00:24:27,700
Yen.

400
00:24:30,267 --> 00:24:32,333
Yen, can we talk?

401
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:34,533
I thought I made myself clear,
Red.

402
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:38,133
What else do we need to talk
about?

403
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:39,800
That was before.

404
00:24:39,867 --> 00:24:41,133
Before I found out that there's
a possibility

405
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:45,333
your mom could be innocent.

406
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:49,067
You don't need to tell me that
because I know she's innocent.

407
00:24:49,133 --> 00:24:50,833
Yen...

408
00:24:50,900 --> 00:24:53,267
I just realized it now.

409
00:24:53,333 --> 00:24:56,200
But can you change our
situation?

410
00:25:01,367 --> 00:25:03,167
- Something happened to Red!
- What?

411
00:25:03,267 --> 00:25:06,500
I'm sorry to say this, Auntie,
but something happened to Red.

412
00:25:06,567 --> 00:25:07,500
What happened?

413
00:25:07,567 --> 00:25:11,133
Eden's not here.

414
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:13,200
She's in the hospital.

415
00:25:13,267 --> 00:25:14,267
What?

416
00:25:14,333 --> 00:25:15,533
She's in the hospital?

417
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:16,967
Why? What happened?

418
00:25:17,033 --> 00:25:20,700
If you're here
for your daughter,

419
00:25:20,767 --> 00:25:23,200
I wish she was in a grave state.

420
00:25:23,267 --> 00:25:26,133
Or instead, I wish she was
with Angelo now.

421
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:27,333
My son whom you murdered.

422
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,600
That way, I can get my revenge
on you.

423
00:25:29,667 --> 00:25:31,900
Oh, really?

424
00:25:31,967 --> 00:25:33,600
You really won't leave me alone!

425
00:25:33,667 --> 00:25:34,600
Don't get my daughter involved!

426
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:36,433
Not my daughter!
